    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1976-01-19T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1976-01-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="83"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d83">
                <head>83. Memorandum From the President’s Assistant for National Security Affairs
                        (<persName corresp="#p_SB_1">Scowcroft</persName>) to President <persName
                        corresp="#p_FG_1">Ford</persName>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d83fn1">
                        <seg type="summary">Summary: <persName corresp="#p_SB_1"
                                >Scowcroft</persName> recommended that <persName corresp="#p_FG_1"
                                >Ford</persName> approve <persName corresp="#p_RD_1"
                                >Rumsfeld</persName>’s proposal to offer an additional 250 Poseidon
                            reentry vehicles for <gloss target="#t_SACEUR_1">SACEUR</gloss>’s
                            General Strike Plan.</seg>
                        <p>
                            <seg type="source">Source: Ford Library, <gloss target="#t_NSC_1"
                                    >NSC</gloss> Institutional Files (H-Files), Box 65, <gloss
                                    target="#t_NSDM_1">NSDM</gloss> 328—Modification of SSBN
                                Commitments to <gloss target="#t_NATO_1">NATO</gloss>. Secret. Sent
                                for action. <persName corresp="#p_FG_1">Ford</persName> initialed
                                his approval of <persName corresp="#p_SB_1">Scowcroft</persName>’s
                                recommendation. Attached but not published is Tab A, a January 16
                                memorandum from <persName corresp="#p_RD_1">Rumsfeld</persName> to
                                    <persName corresp="#p_SB_1">Scowcroft</persName> entitled,
                                “Modification of Poseidon Commitment to <gloss target="#t_NATO_1"
                                    >NATO</gloss>.”</seg>
                        </p>
                    </note>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1976-01-19"
                        >January 19, 1976</date>.</dateline>
                <list type="subject">
                    <head>SUBJECT</head>
                    <item>Modification of Poseidon Commitment to <gloss target="#t_NATO_1"
                            >NATO</gloss>
                    </item>
                </list>
                <p>Since 1972 the Supreme Allied Commander Europe (<gloss target="#t_SACEUR_1"
                        >SACEUR</gloss>) has had designated 150 of the reentry vehicles carried on
                    the ballistic missiles of the U.S. Poseidon submarine fleet to cover targets in
                        <gloss target="#t_NATO_1">NATO</gloss>’s General Strike Plan (<gloss
                        target="#t_GSP_1">GSP</gloss>). Secretary <persName corresp="#p_RD_1"
                        >Rumsfeld</persName> would like to announce this week at a meeting of the
                        <gloss target="#t_NATO_1">NATO</gloss> Nuclear Planning Group a U.S. offer
                    to assign an additional 250 reentry vehicles for <gloss target="#t_GSP_1"
                        >GSP</gloss> targets, bringing the total number of RVs assigned to <gloss
                        target="#t_SACEUR_1">SACEUR</gloss> to 400 (memo at Tab A).</p>
                <p>I have reviewed the proposal and concur in it. The Poseidon RVs provide <gloss
                        target="#t_SACEUR_1">SACEUR</gloss> with a secure and reliable way to cover
                        <gloss target="#t_GSP_1">GSP</gloss> targets, and an increase in the number
                    of RVs dedicated to these targets will introduce some flexibility into the use
                    that can be made of other nuclear systems in Europe. Making the offer at the
                    Nuclear Planning Group meeting will give Secretary <persName corresp="#p_RD_1"
                        >Rumsfeld</persName> a chance to explain the offer in the context of our
                    general approach to <gloss target="#t_NATO_1">NATO</gloss>’s theater nuclear
                    forces, and to initiate the studies required to incorporate this increased
                    capability into <gloss target="#t_NATO_1">NATO</gloss>’s overall force
                    posture.</p>
                <p rend="sectiontitleital">Recommendation:</p>
                <p>That you authorize Secretary <persName corresp="#p_RD_1">Rumsfeld</persName> to
                    offer an additional 250 Poseidon reentry vehicles for <gloss
                        target="#t_SACEUR_1">SACEUR</gloss>’s General Strike Plan at the upcoming
                        <gloss target="#t_NATO_1">NATO</gloss> Nuclear Planning Group meeting.
                    (Secretary <persName corresp="#p_KHA_1">Kissinger</persName> concurs.)</p>
            </div>
